[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1217},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F15\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F15\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F15\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F15\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react\u002F":1193,"related:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F15\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react\u002F":1202},"\u002Freact\u002F20220915\u002F517969418\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1170,"date":1171,"description":1172,"extension":1173,"lang":1174,"meta":1175,"navigation":206,"path":1176,"readingMinutes":1177,"seo":1178,"standalone":1179,"stem":1180,"tags":1181,"tldr":1190,"updated":1171,"url":1191,"__hash__":1192},"content\u002Fen\u002FReact\u002Freact-day-01-what-is-react.md","You'll Have to Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now? - React Basics - What Even Is React? - (1)","1002882519",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1163},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,43,49,56,61,64,67,76,86,89,102,117,128,132,135,140,143,150,153,157,160,163,166,339,452,463,466,469,472,665,689,694,697,700,703,709,712,715,868,958,963,966,1098,1120,1125,1128,1131,1134,1137,1140,1143,1147,1150,1159],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"No matter what, you've got to start by getting comfortable with React's basic concepts and a little bit of its background. That groundwork makes it much easier to spot the differences when you go pick up other frameworks later. On top of that, I'm a Vue developer myself, so honestly I'm writing this with the mindset of someone who just wants to add one more framework to the toolbox. That means you'll probably see a few side-by-side comparisons between Vue and React syntax along the way — mostly because I want fellow Vue devs to have an easier time getting started. Okay, enough preamble. Let's get into it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"what-even-is-react","What even is React?",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"The React official site actually tells you straight up that it's a ",[28,29,30],"strong",{},"JavaScript Library"," — a library of JavaScript functions. Notice that? What I wrote there is a library, not a framework.",[17,33,34,35,42],{},"You can head over to the ",[36,37,41],"a",{"href":38,"rel":39},"https:\u002F\u002Freactjs.org\u002F",[40],"nofollow","React official site"," and check for yourself, because that's genuinely what it says.",[17,44,45],{},[46,47],"img",{"alt":30,"src":48},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002FReactJS.png",[17,50,51,52,55],{},"Vue's official site, on the other hand, says it's a ",[28,53,54],{},"JavaScript Framework",".",[17,57,58],{},[46,59],{"alt":54,"src":60},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002FVueJS.png",[17,62,63],{},"At this point you might be wondering...",[17,65,66],{},"\"What about Angular? What's Angular? I don't see it written on its site.\"",[17,68,69,70,75],{},"Angular is also a JavaScript Framework (Vue is basically what you get when the author cherry-picked the good parts of Angular and built a framework out of them). It's just that Angular's official site doesn't explicitly spell out what it is. But we can find this line over on the ",[36,71,74],{"href":72,"rel":73},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FAngular_(web_framework)",[40],"Wikipedia page",":",[77,78,79],"blockquote",{},[17,80,81,82,85],{},"Angular is a TypeScript-based free and open-source ",[28,83,84],{},"web application framework"," led by the Angular Team at Google and by a community of individuals and corporations",[17,87,88],{},"So we can quickly sum up the categories of the three big frameworks:",[90,91,92,96,99],"ul",{},[93,94,95],"li",{},"Vue → JavaScript Framework",[93,97,98],{},"React → JavaScript Library",[93,100,101],{},"Angular → JavaScript Framework",[17,103,104,105,108,109,111,112,116],{},"Every now and then you might hear people say ",[28,106,107],{},"VAR",", ",[28,110,107],{}," — and that VAR is just the first letters of these three big names mashed together (definitely not the ",[113,114,115],"code",{},"var"," you use to declare variables).",[90,118,119,122,125],{},[93,120,121],{},"V -> Vue",[93,123,124],{},"A -> Angular",[93,126,127],{},"R -> React",[12,129,131],{"id":130},"framework-library","Framework? Library?",[17,133,134],{},"Quick summary up front:",[77,136,137],{},[17,138,139],{},"A Framework hands you a complete architecture and a full solution. A Library is something you have to assemble and wire up the architecture and solutions yourself.",[17,141,142],{},"To put it in more human terms: think of a Framework as walking into a home-improvement store, picking out the furniture, and ordering a whole kitchen-and-bathroom set. The store's crew shows up at your place and builds the exact kitchen-and-bathroom combo you wanted.",[17,144,145,146,149],{},"A Library is more of a ",[28,147,148],{},"do-it-yourself"," deal. Picture going to the same store and buying the ready-made parts — the bathtub, the tiles, the range hood, and so on — but the catch is you've got to put it all together yourself. That's your classic DIY.",[17,151,152],{},"I won't go deeper into this point here.",[12,154,156],{"id":155},"vue-vs-react-differences","Vue vs React differences",[17,158,159],{},"The examples coming up are just for you to glance at — no need to rush to understand them. We'll walk through everything slowly later on.",[17,161,162],{},"So let's take a quick look at how Vue and React differ. First up, Vue as the example. Here's the basic Vue structure:",[17,164,165],{},"(Using Vue 3 Options API for this one)",[167,168,173],"pre",{"className":169,"code":170,"language":171,"meta":172,"style":172},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","const { createApp } = Vue;\n\nconst app = createApp({\n  data() {\n    return {\n      count: 0,\n    };\n  },\n  methods: {\n    sayHi() {\n      window.alert('Hello Ray.');\n    },\n  },\n});\n\napp.mount('#app');\n","js","",[113,174,175,201,208,226,235,244,256,262,268,274,282,301,307,312,318,323],{"__ignoreMap":172},[176,177,180,184,188,192,195,198],"span",{"class":178,"line":179},"line",1,[176,181,183],{"class":182},"sOudu","const",[176,185,187],{"class":186},"s8XSl"," { ",[176,189,191],{"class":190},"stw71","createApp",[176,193,194],{"class":186}," } ",[176,196,197],{"class":182},"=",[176,199,200],{"class":186}," Vue;\n",[176,202,204],{"class":178,"line":203},2,[176,205,207],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":206},true,"\n",[176,209,211,213,216,219,223],{"class":178,"line":210},3,[176,212,183],{"class":182},[176,214,215],{"class":190}," app",[176,217,218],{"class":182}," =",[176,220,222],{"class":221},"scAaK"," createApp",[176,224,225],{"class":186},"({\n",[176,227,229,232],{"class":178,"line":228},4,[176,230,231],{"class":221},"  data",[176,233,234],{"class":186},"() {\n",[176,236,238,241],{"class":178,"line":237},5,[176,239,240],{"class":182},"    return",[176,242,243],{"class":186}," {\n",[176,245,247,250,253],{"class":178,"line":246},6,[176,248,249],{"class":186},"      count: ",[176,251,252],{"class":190},"0",[176,254,255],{"class":186},",\n",[176,257,259],{"class":178,"line":258},7,[176,260,261],{"class":186},"    };\n",[176,263,265],{"class":178,"line":264},8,[176,266,267],{"class":186},"  },\n",[176,269,271],{"class":178,"line":270},9,[176,272,273],{"class":186},"  methods: {\n",[176,275,277,280],{"class":178,"line":276},10,[176,278,279],{"class":221},"    sayHi",[176,281,234],{"class":186},[176,283,285,288,291,294,298],{"class":178,"line":284},11,[176,286,287],{"class":186},"      window.",[176,289,290],{"class":221},"alert",[176,292,2