ss":353},[176,1109,358],{"class":357},[176,1111,197],{"class":186},[176,1113,363],{"class":296},[176,1115,684],{"class":186},[176,1117,354],{"class":353},[176,1119,366],{"class":186},[453,1121,1124],{"height":455,"style":456,"scrolling":457,"title":1122,"src":1123,"frameBorder":457,"loading":460,"allowTransparency":461,"allowFullScreen":461},"(4)React Hook init","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FvYRrvyE?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FvYRrvyE\">\n  (4)React Hook init\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,1126,1127],{},"At this point you might be curious...",[17,1129,1130],{},"\"So which style are we actually learning?\"",[17,1132,1133],{},"This whole series centers on React Hooks, so the earlier examples were just there to give you a feel for the various ways you can write React and Vue. From comparing the two, you can see they're growing more and more alike — which conveniently answers a question a lot of people wrestle with:",[17,1135,1136],{},"\"Which framework should I learn first?\"",[17,1138,1139],{},"Honestly, either is fine. Just focus on learning one really well, and when you go look at the other afterward, you'll find it pretty easy to pick up, because there's so much overlap.",[17,1141,1142],{},"That's it for this one. See you in the next post.",[12,1144,1146],{"id":1145},"afterword","Afterword",[17,1148,1149],{},"This post is also published on my blog:",[90,1151,1152],{},[93,1153,1154],{},[36,1155,1158],{"href":1156,"rel":1157},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002F",[40],"It's Ray, not Array",[1160,1161,1162],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sOudu, html code.shiki .sOudu{--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-default:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .s8XSl, html code.shiki .s8XS